  "texts": [
    "DrAttack uses simple fruit names to replace the malicious words and then reverse the mapping to postprocess the responses.",
    "This can results in false positive jailbreaks due to the postprocessing reintroducing the malicious words even when the jailbreak fails.",
    "In the example from the table, the \"a bomb\" is in fact a banana and the tutorial is for making banana smoothie.",
    "In WordGame and WordGame+, however, such issues are highly unlikely as we do not use hypothetical scenarios or meaningful words to replace the malicious ones.",
    "Quite the opposite, both our prompt and responses are fully separable -the word game, the auxiliary task and the auxiliary questions never intertwine with the malicious request and its response."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}